Although the perinuclear ring is regarded as the microtubule-organizing center for the manchette, findings about the nucleation site and the direction of microtubules are inconsistent. During spermatid differentiation, the manchette moves toward the tail neck region, with constriction of the perinuclear ring, which contributes to sculpting of the sperm head in mice.
